U.S.- S. Korea Joint Military Exercises Slammed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed commentary. It goes on:
 These war maneuvers are a preliminary war and a test nuclear war designed to finally examine and round off the preparations for a war against the north and mount a preemptive nuclear attack on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This large-scale saber-rattling cannot but be a very dangerous development as it is timed to coincide with the U.S. ever-increasing pressure and escalating conspiratorial plots against the DPRK. 
 The U.S. has not only tightened its financial sanctions against the DPRK and intensified the "human rights" offensive against it but escalated its smear campaign against Pyongyang. As if it were not enough with these moves, it is crying out for a preemptive attack on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is due to the frantic moves of the U.S. against the DPRK that the six-party talks still remain stalled and confrontation and tensions are festering on the Korean Peninsula.
 The DPRK has already warned the U.S. and south Korea against the serious consequences to be entailed by these war gambles and strongly demanded a halt to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a matter of fact, the U.S. imperialists' saber-rattling has made the prospects of the peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue and the six-party talks gloomier, thrown more obstacles to the process of improving the inter-Korean relations and compelled the north to postpone the inter-Korean ministerial talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are a chief disturber of peace, a chieftain of war and a cursed foe of national unity and the reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will stake their lives at the dignity of the nation and the cause of reunification and frustrate the intention of the United States and its allies to invade the DPRK, going against the desire of the Korean nation and the trend of the times, the commentary concludes.

S. Korean Men of Literature and Art Vow to Struggle against Expansion of U.S. Forces Base 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- A "literary and art festival for peace" and a "candle-light cultural festival" reportedly took place in Taechu-ri, Phyongthaek City, Kyonggi Province in south Korea on Mar. 25. Poets, moviemen and residents there present at those events strongly protested the expansion of the U.S. forces base.
 They were co-sponsored by the "Literary Forum for Peace of south Korea," the "General Federation of National Artistes of south Korea" and the Joint Action of Men of Literature and Art.    Participants in the "literary and art festival for peace" staged a performance, while reciting a poem dealing with the actions of the residents in Phyongthaek to defend their cradle, shouting slogans such as "No expansion of U.S. military base!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the 571st "candle-light cultural festival" said that an anti-U.S. struggle is the only way of protecting their literature, declaring that when the people of all social standings pool their efforts, they will surely emerge victorious in their actions against the expansion of the base. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A statement read out at the function warned if the south Korean authorities use force to offer the area of Phyongthaek to the U.S. forces, all the men of literature and art would struggle against it to the last ounce of their strength.

Application of Double-standards to Nuclear Issue Cannot Be Allowed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- The U.S. should not apply its unreasonable double-standards to the nuclear issue but dismantle its nuclear weapons first of all and stop its moves to threaten other countries with nuclear weapons and mount a preemptive attack, says Rodong Sinmun Thursday in a signed article.
 The article castigates the U.S. for applying unreasonable double-standards to the nuclear issue, while pursuing its aggressive and hegemonic nuclear politics turning a deaf ear to the voices of humankind demanding total dismantlement of nukes. It is the consistent military policy and strategic target of the U.S. imperialists to bolster up nuclear forces and hold nuclear supremacy, the article says, and goes on:
 The U.S. imperialists, considering nukes as almighty means for establishing world domination order, are threatening other countries with them and bringing in dark clouds of a nuclear war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. application of double-standards to the nuclear issue finds its expression in conniving, patronizing and assisting its allies' development and production of nuclear weapons while kicking up a row of pressure on those countries whose ideology and system are different from its own over the "nuclear issue".                                  The U.S. is applying double-standards to the nuclear issue according to state relations with itself and its strategic interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. double-dealing attitude in the nuclear issue is a revelation of its unilateralism and highhandedness. Its unreasonable behavior weakens the binding force of the NPT and drives the world to a nuclear arms race. Its nuclear highhandedness reduces the NPT to a good-for-nothing and eggs nuclear-free countries to have nuclear means. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is talking about "non-proliferation" while stepping up nuclear arms buildup and modernization and openly pursuing a nuclear war because it has a sinister intension to make anti-imperialist and independent countries victims of its nuclear hard-line policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. anti-DPRK campaign over the nuclear issue of the Korean Peninsula is a typical example of its application of double-standards to the nuclear issue.
 It is the unfair application of double-standards that the U.S. is scheming to completely check the peaceful nuclear activities of the DPRK, while announcing that it will provide nuclear technique and fuel to some countries outside the NPT.

Kim Il Sung Praised as Great Man 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- Erich Zavadil, chairman of the Austrian preparatory committee for commemorating the Day of the Sun, addressing a meeting, said that President Kim Il Sung was a great man recognized by the world, adding that the progressive people of many countries significantly commemorate the day in every April.
 Various functions took place in Democratic Congo, Tanzania and Austria from Mar. 18 to 22 on the occasion with leading officials and members of political parties and organizations of those countries attending. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Several figures including Otete Gaston Mboyo, chairman of the National Committee of the Genuine Lumumbist Patriotic Party of Democratic Congo, at a remembrance meeting recalled that the President made undying contributions to the Korean revolution and the accomplishment of the human cause of independence and extended full support to the people of the developing countries in their struggle for national liberation and the building of a new society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Praising the President as a "great politician of the 20th century", "a peerlessly great man" and "the great sun of humankind", they stressed that his exploits would shine forever with his august name. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the Group for the Study of Kimilsungism of Mjumbe University in Morogoro, Tanzania, at a reading session under the title "President Kim Il Sung who made a great contribution to the human cause of independence" said that the President built the most advantageous socialist system in the DPRK by embodying the immortal Juche idea, a guiding idea in the era of independence, and made an undying contribution to the struggle of the world oppressed people including the African people for freedom and liberation.

Study of Juche Idea and Songun Politics Brisk in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- The study and dissemination of the Juche idea and Songun politics have been brisk involving diverse forms and methods in nearly 30 countries for the last three months.
 Leader Kim Jong Il's famous works "On Having a Correct Viewpoint and Understanding of the Juche Philosophy" and "The Juche Philosophy Is an Original Revolutionary Philosophy" were published in booklet by the Mt. Paektu Association for Independent Development of Mongolia and the Publiraser Publishing House of Peru.
 Books "Cause of Juche and Songun Politics", "Homeland of Songun Politics" and "Might of Songun" came off the press in Nepal, Pakistan and Italy. These books profoundly explained the principles and originality of the Juche idea and Songun politics, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seminars on Kim Jong Il's works on the Juche idea and Songun politics including "On the Juche Idea" and "Songun Politics of Our Party Is an Effective Socialist Political Mode" were held in Russia, Mongolia, India, Guinea, Uganda, Mexico, Austria and other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And seminars, lectures and round-table talks on the Juche idea and Songun politics were held in different countries including Syria, Bangladesh, Thailand, Tajikistan, Sweden, Moldova, Tanzania, Democratic Congo and Brazil. 
 The Ethiopian Youth Committee for the Study of the Juche idea was formed in Addis Ababa for the purpose of intensifying the study and dissemination of the Juche idea on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, media in different countries gave wide publicity to the great Juche idea and Songun politics under the titles "Kim Jong Il and the immortal feats performed by him for the human cause of independence", "Modern Korea and Songun", "Songun politics and political power" and others.

Samilpho Foodstuff Processing Factory
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- The Samilpho Foodstuff Processing Factory, located in Raknang District in Pyongyang, is a leading food processing center which is conducive to improving the dietary life and health of working people.
 The factory, built in August Juche 85 (1996), covers thousands of square meters of area. It has been furnished with a complete set of modern machinery and equipment in accordance with the assembly-line production processes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It produces hundreds of kinds of processed foodstuffs including tea, spirits, noodle and processed local farm products. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tea workshop of the factory turns out various kinds of tea with highland special products and tonics and health food with natural honey. And the spirits workshop distils Koryo medicinal spirits of over 50 kinds including Kumgangsan Balloonflower Liquor, Rokyongsansam Liquor and Chilbosan Mushroom Liquor with natural medicinal materials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, Pyongyang Buckwheat Cold Noodle, Arrowroot Cold Noodle, Elm Cold Noodle, Koryo Insam (ginseng) Honey, Pullo Sansam (wild ginseng) Honey and Bee Milk Honey manufactured by the factory are popular with people for their peculiar taste and ardor and their high medicinal effect. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its processed foodstuffs are demanded by Korean people at home and abroad and foreigners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jong Yun Ho, manager of the factory, told KCNA that the production processes of the factory are perfect in the technical aspect. The factory will do its bit by increasing the sorts of health food and tonics with famous natural products indigenous to Korea as raw materials, he added.

Books on Cultural Heritage Published in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- The Cultural Preservation Agency of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has recently published books "Companion of Cultural Heritage Protectors" and "Ryongthong Temple in Kaesong", introducing the cultural heritage of the nation.
 The book "Companion of Cultural Heritage Protectors" gives the chronological table of the on-the-spot guidance of President Kim Il Sung, leader Kim Jong Il and anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk over cultural relics. It also introduces main historical relics and remains belonging to the primitive, ancient and mediaeval ages and methods for preserving and managing them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Featured in it are general knowledge, chronological table of the Korean history and main historical relics in different regions for the working people and school youth and children. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The book "Ryongthong Temple in Kaesong" writes that Kim Jong Il gave instructions related to the work for restoring the famous Ryongthong Temple of Koryo on more than ten occasions and energetically guided the project in the period of "Arduous March" and the forced march and the temple was successfully restored to the original state.
 It also compiles the position of the temple before the restoration and its history, career of Friar of attainment of divine enlightenment Ui Chon who lived as the monk in the temple for a long time, relics which remained there and the literary and art works related with the temple. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also introduces in detail the entrance of the newly restored temple, courtyard, main area of the temple, grave site of Ui Chon, memorial service hall area and epitaph written on his gravestone.
